{
  "stem": "13469.7",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 18.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in August he found out-- we came to Holland in June, July-- in August he found out where we were.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he was in the British army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he came over to visit us in Holland in September, and he offered to take us back, or get us back into England.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we said yes, you know, we, we wanted to do that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Eve-- he took Eve back to England straight away, because she had her British birth certificate.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had no problems.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But for [NON-ENGLISH] and me, we couldn't go to England without a visa.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we stayed on in Laren for some further time, in fact, for several months.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in the meantime, my uncle and aunt got these entry visas for us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And on the 23rd of November, 1945-- seven months exactly after we'd been liberated in Trebitz, we got to Harridge and on the boat train to Liverpool Street Station.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there my uncle and Eve met us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in some ways, that's really the end of the story, unless we're going to carry on after the war.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You want to carry on?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I want to carry on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "What was it like being in England again?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very nice, I would say, I would say.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, it was really, in many ways, much better than being in Holland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because in Holland, we were in an orphanage.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And although we got on with the other kids and went to school and all that sort of thing, we could feel, now, that we hadn't got our parents, and we couldn't really figure out our life.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was very nice to have family around us again.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
